name: Minestrone Soup in a Jar
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable stock base'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1 (15', 'unit': 'ounce) can', 'name': 'kidney beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shell pasta'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green beans'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped sweet onion'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'carrot'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'celery'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese, for garnish'}
steps: Stir together vegetable stock base, tomato paste, minced garlic, and Italian seasoning in a small bowl. Divide mixture evenly among 3 microwave-safe pint-size canning jars with lids.. Layer evenly with kidney beans, ditalini pasta, green beans, onion, carrot, and celery. Chill, covered, up to 5 days. To serve, see “Heat and Eat,” below. Garnish with grated Parmesan.

name: Classic Minestrone Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced onion'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced carrot'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced celery'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'minced fresh rosemary'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'Contadina® Tomato Sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'cannellini beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'College Inn® Chicken Broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced zucchini'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dry ditalini pasta'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh Italian parsley'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'shredded Parmesan cheese, or to taste'}
steps: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Sauté onion, carrot, celery, garlic, and rosemary until vegetables begin to soften, about 5 minutes.. Stir in tomato sauce, beans, water, broth, zucchini, pasta, and pepper; bring to a simmer. Cook, uncovered and stirring occasionally, until pasta is tender, 10 minutes. Stir in parsley. Serve topped with Parmesan and additional parsley if desired.

name: Chicken Minestrone Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breast, cut into bite-sized pieces'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced carrot'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped celery'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken stock'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes with basil, garlic, and oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'cannellini beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'kidney beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 ounce) can', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'zucchini, quartered lengthwise and cut into 1/2 inch slices'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'frozen cut green beans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ditalini pasta'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese, or more to taste (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley'}
steps: Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add chicken to pot, and sauté just until lightly browned, about 3 minutes. Remove chicken from pot; set aside.. Heat remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil in the pot; add onions and cook until translucent, about 3 minutes. Stir in garlic; cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add carrots and celery; cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.. Reduce heat to medium-low; stir in chicken stock, diced tomatoes, cannellini beans, kidney beans, tomato paste, zucchini, green beans, Italian seasoning. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.. Stir in chicken and ditalini pasta, and cook until pasta is tender yet firm to the bite, about 8 minutes. Season to taste with salt and black pepper. If soup is too thick, add a little water or stock. Garnish each bowl with Parmesan and parsley.

name: Jamie's Minestrone Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onions, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chopped celery'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': '', 'name': 'carrots, sliced'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'tomato sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red wine (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'zucchinis, quartered and sliced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'baby spinach, rinsed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'fresh or frozen green beans, cut into 1 ½-inch pieces'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'canned kidney beans, drained'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh basil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped fresh oregano'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shell pasta'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese for topping'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}
steps: Gather the ingredients.. Heat olive oil in a large stockpot over medium-low heat. Sauté garlic in hot oil until fragrant, 2 to 3 minutes. Add onion; cook and stir until translucent, 4 to 5 minutes.. Add celery and carrots; sauté for 1 to 2 minutes.. Pour in tomato sauce, broth, and water; bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Add red wine; reduce heat to low.. Stir in zucchini, spinach, green beans, kidney beans, basil, oregano, salt, and pepper. Simmer until soup is heated through, 30 to 40 minutes.. Meanwhile, fill a medium saucepan with water and bring to a boil. Cook seashell pasta in boiling water, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, 7 to 8 minutes. Drain and set aside.. Place 2 tablespoons cooked pasta into individual serving bowls. Ladle soup over pasta and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.. Drizzle with olive oil to serve.

steps: Heat olive oil in a large pot or Dutch oven over medium-high heat until shimmering. Add celery, carrots, and onion. Cook, stirring frequently, until onion begins to turn translucent, about 4 minutes. Add garlic and stir until fragrant, about 30 seconds.. Add vegetable broth, marinara sauce, tomato paste, and Italian seasoning. Stir to combine. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, uncovered, until carrots are soft, about 10 minutes.. Add pasta and zucchini. Cook until pasta is tender, about 10 minutes. Stir in beans, kale, salt, and pepper. Remove from heat and allow soup to cool slightly. Spoon into individual bowls and garnish with Parmesan cheese.

name: Best Darn Minestrone Soup Around
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chopped onions'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(15 ounce) cans', 'name': 'mixed vegetables, with liquid'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(14 ounce) cans', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(16 ounce) cans', 'name': 'kidney beans, with liquid'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) cans', 'name': 'whole peeled tomatoes, with liquid'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen chopped spinach'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'uncooked elbow macaroni'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'canned garbanzo beans, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese, divided'}, {'quantity': '4 ¼', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'dried parsley'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried basil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Melt butter in a large stock pot over medium heat. Add onions and sauté until soft. Add mixed vegetables, broth, kidney beans, tomatoes, spinach, and tomato paste; simmer gently for 1 1/2 hours.. Use a slotted spoon to transfer about 1/2 of the vegetables to a blender or food processor, reserving the liquid in the stockpot. Purée vegetables until smooth, then return to the pot.. name: Instant Pot Hearty Minestrone Soup

steps: Heat oil in a multi-functional pressure cooker (such as Instant Pot) on Sauté mode. Add beef and onion; cook until beef is no longer pink on the outside, about 4 minutes. Add green beans, celery, carrot, garlic, oregano, dried basil, and black pepper; stir to combine.. Add broth, diced tomatoes, and crushed tomatoes to the Pot; stir to combine. Select Soup setting; close and lock the lid. Select High pressure according to manufacturer's instructions; set timer for 35 minutes. Allow 10 to 15 minutes for pressure to build.. Release pressure carefully using the quick-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, about 5 minutes. Unlock and remove the lid. Stir in kidney beans and pasta. Turn on Slow Cook mode; cook according manufacturer's instructions until vegetables and pasta are tender, about 10 minutes. Season with salt. Ladle soup into bowls; top with Parmesan cheese and fresh basil.

steps: In a large soup pot, combine vegetable stock, undrained tomatoes, potato, onion, celery, carrot, cabbage, and Italian seasoning. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Simmer for about 15 minutes.. Stir in beans, corn, zucchini, and pasta; simmer for 10 to 15 more minutes until the vegetables are tender. Season with salt and pepper.

name: Classic Minestrone
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'leek, sliced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'carrots, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'zucchini, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'green beans, cut into 1-inch pieces'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'quarts', 'name': 'vegetable stock'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'chopped tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped fresh thyme'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'cannellini beans, undrained'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'elbow macaroni'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Heat olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add leek, carrots, zucchini, green beans, and celery. Cover, reduce the heat to low, and cook for 15 minutes, shaking the pan occasionally.. Uncover and stir in stock, tomatoes, and thyme; bring to a boil. Cover again, reduce the heat to low, and simmer gently for 30 minutes.. Stir in undrained cannellini beans and pasta. Simmer for an additional 10 minutes, or until pasta is tender yet firm to the bite. Season with salt and pepper before serving.

name: Tortellini Minestrone Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'Italian sausage'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'low-sodium chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) can', 'name': 'whole peeled tomatoes, cut into pieces'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'thinly sliced carrots'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'thinly sliced celery'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ketchup'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dry red wine'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(9 ounce) package', 'name': 'refrigerated cheese tortellini'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'thinly sliced zucchini'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese, or to taste'}
steps: Heat a Dutch oven or large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir sausage in the Dutch oven until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes; drain and discard grease. Add onion and garlic; cook and stir until onion is tender, 5 to 10 minutes.. Stir chicken broth, tomatoes, carrots, celery, ketchup, and red wine into sausage mixture; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer until carrots and celery are tender, about 30 minutes. Add tortellini and zucchini to the soup and cover; simmer until zucchini are tender, 25 to 30 more minutes. Ladle soup into serving bowls and top with Parmesan cheese.

name: Green Minestrone
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'white onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, pressed'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'frozen cut green beans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'frozen peas'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'zucchini, chopped'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'vegetable broth'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'minced fresh rosemary'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked great Northern beans'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ditalini pasta'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'minced fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil, or as needed'}
steps: Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a heavy-bottomed pot over medium-high heat; cook and stir onion and garlic until onion is translucent, about 10 minutes. Add green beans, peas, and zucchini; toss to coat vegetables with oil.. Slowly stream vegetable broth into vegetable mixture; bring to a simmer over medium heat. Stir in rosemary and great Northern beans and bring back to a simmer, about 5 minutes. Add ditalini pasta and simmer soup until pasta is tender but firm to the bite and soup has thickened, 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in parsley.. Ladle soup into serving bowls and top each serving with 1 heaping tablespoon Parmesan cheese; season with salt and black pepper. Garnish soup with a drizzle of extra-virgin olive oil.

name: Minestrone Soup II

steps: Turn on a multi-functional pressure cooker (such as Instant Pot) and select Saute function. Add sausage and sauté, breaking it into pieces with a wooden spoon, until browned, about 5 minutes. steps: Combine milk, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, and salt in a large bowl. Add ground beef and mix well. Shape into 36 to 48 meatballs.. Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Combine beef broth, tomatoes, corn, celery, cabbage, onion, zucchini, wine, parsley, oregano, basil, garlic powder, salt, and pepper in a large pot. Stir in browned meatballs. name: Gluten-Free Northern Italian Autumn Minestrone
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cranberry beans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'carrot'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'yellow onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'stalk', 'name': 'celery'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'red bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '15', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'potatoes, peeled and diced'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'diced carrots'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'zucchini, diced'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'fresh pumpkin, diced'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'diced yellow onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'minced fresh rosemary'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'bay leaf'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'vegetable broth, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'gluten-free elbow pasta'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'fresh hot pepper, minced'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'finely grated Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese (Optional)'}
steps: Place cranberry beans into a large container and cover with several inches of cool water; let soak, 8 hours to overnight. Drain.. Shred carrot, yellow onion, celery, and red pepper in a food processor to create a sofrito mixture.. Heat oil in a 7-quart pressure cooker over medium-high heat. Add sofrito mixture and saute until softened, 3 to 5 minutes. Add soaked beans, potatoes, diced carrots, zucchini, pumpkin, and diced onion. Cook and stir until warmed through, 3 to 5 minutes more. Add oregano, rosemary, and bay leaf. Stir well to coat vegetables with oil and seasonings.. Add enough broth to cover vegetables by 1 inch. Close the pressure cooker lid and bring up to pressure, about 10 minutes. Cook an additional 10 minutes from the first whistle.. Allow pressure to release naturally and remove lid, about 10 minutes. Taste and adjust salt if necessary. Add additional broth to allow for cooking the pasta. Bring to a boil and add pasta. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender but still firm to the bite, about 8 minutes. Add more boiling broth if needed during cooking.. Ladle soup into bowls and top with minced hot pepper and Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese.

name: Hearty Vegetarian Minestrone
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'carrots, diced'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, diced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(10 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen cut green beans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried basil'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'crushed tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'vegetable broth'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'kidney beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'cannellini beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'elbow macaroni'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegan shredded Parmesan-style cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh basil'}
steps: Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add onion and cook until soft, about 3 minutes. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add carrots and celery; cook and stir until soft, 5 to 6 minutes.. Stir in green beans, oregano, basil, salt, and pepper; cook for about 5 minutes. Add diced and crushed tomatoes and vegetable broth; bring to a boil. If it looks too thick, add a bit of water.. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes. Stir in kidney beans, cannellini beans, and macaroni; cook until pasta is tender yet firm to the bite, 7 to 10 minutes. Taste and adjust salt and pepper, if needed.. Ladle into bowls and garnish with Parmesan-style cheese and fresh basil.

name: Prosciutto Fave Minestrone alla Riso
ingredients: {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'bacon, chopped'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced cooked ham'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large stalks', 'name': 'celery, thinly sliced, leaves reserved and chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'carrots, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, crushed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) can', 'name': 'whole peeled tomatoes, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'quart', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown rice'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'cranberry beans, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'white beans, drained'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley'}
steps: In a large pot over medium heat, cook bacon in olive oil until brown. Stir in ham and cook a few minutes more. Stir in celery (reserve the leaves), onion and carrot and cook until vegetables are tender, 5 minutes. Stir in garlic and cook 1 minute more.. Stir in tomatoes, broth, rice, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes, or until vegetables are soft and rice is nearly tender.. Stir in cranberry beans and white beans and heat through. Stir in parsley and celery leaves and remove from heat. Serve hot.

name: Red Winter Minestrone with Winter Greens Pesto
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'beet greens'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'turnip greens'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'kale'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'ounce', 'name': 'Parmigiano Reggiano cheese, grated'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'white onion, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Roma (plum) tomatoes, peeled and grated'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'minced fresh rosemary'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'bay leaf'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'dried chili flakes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'leek, white and light green parts only, halved lengthwise, cleaned, and cut into 1/2-inch slices'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'carrot, peeled and sliced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'turnips, peeled and cubed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'beets, peeled and cubed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dry white wine'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked cannellini beans'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green beans, cut into 1-inch pieces'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped flat-leaf (Italian) parsley'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fresh lemon juice, or to taste (Optional)'}
steps: Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Prepare a bowl of ice water. Strip beet greens, turnip greens, and kale from their coarse stems and wash leaves well. Working in batches, cook each bunch in boiling water until bright green and slightly limp, about 1 minute. Transfer immediately to ice water and repeat with remaining greens. Discard cooking water.. Remove greens from ice water and squeeze out as much water as possible.. Combine greens, 2/3 cup olive oil, 2 cloves garlic, Parmigiano Reggiano cheese, and 1/2 teaspoon kosher salt in blender or food processor; blend until smooth. Transfer pesto to a bowl and cover surface with plastic wrap.. Heat 1/4 cup olive oil in large pot over medium-high heat. Stir in onion, grated tomato, 4 cloves minced garlic, rosemary, 1/2 teaspoon kosher salt, bay leaf, and chili flakes. Cook, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes; reduce heat to low. Continue cooking and stirring until vegetables are a deep golden brown, 20 to 30 minutes.. Pour remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil over onion mixture. Stir in leek, carrot, turnips, and beets. Increase heat to medium-high and cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.. Pour white wine over vegetable mixture and scrape browned bits off the bottom of the pot. Mix cannellini beans and green beans into vegetable mixture; pour in 5 cups water. Bring liquid to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer until green beans are tender, about 5 minutes more. Stir in parsley and lemon juice.. Divide soup among heated bowls and serve with a generous dollop of the winter greens pesto.

name: Mama Kathy's Minestrone
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(14 ounce) cans', 'name': 'stewed tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'tomato sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'baby peas'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely chopped carrots'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'chopped spinach, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'beef bouillon cube'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'uncooked elbow macaroni'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}
steps: Place the beef, onion, and garlic in a skillet over medium heat. Cook until beef is evenly brown and onion is tender. Drain grease.. Transfer beef, onion, and garlic to a large pot. Mix in tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, peas, carrots, spinach, bouillon cube, and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low, and cook 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Add more water or tomato sauce as needed.. Stir macaroni into the soup. Season with Italian seasoning. Continue cooking 10 minutes, or until macaroni is tender.

name: Fall Minestrone Soup

steps: Heat butter in a large pot over medium heat; cook and stir onion and garlic until onion is transparent, 5 to 10 minutes. Add chicken stock, beef broth, and water; bring to a simmer. name: Easy Slow Cooker Vegetarian Minestrone
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'zucchini, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'carrot, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'stalk', 'name': 'celery, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'vegetable stock'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'chickpeas, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'undrained diced tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'fresh green beans, trimmed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'uncooked ditalini pasta'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pesto'}

name: Spruced-Up Slow Cooker Minestrone Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(15 ounce) cans', 'name': 'Southwestern-flavored pinto beans (such as Ranch Style®)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(10.75 ounce) cans', 'name': 'condensed minestrone soup'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'whole kernel corn, undrained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'green beans, undrained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes, undrained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes and green chiles (such as RO*TEL®), undrained'}
steps: Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir ground beef in the hot skillet until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes. Drain and discard grease. Transfer beef to a slow cooker..
